# Visibility baseline capture (phase 57)
# Raw auth bytes and checkpoint state MUST NEVER be committed — they contain
# unredacted PII (emails, phones, names, addresses). The Redact function in
# internal/visbaseline/ produces the safe-to-commit form; raw bytes go to
# /tmp or an explicit .raw-auth/ staging directory.
/tmp/pdb-vis-capture-*
testdata/visibility-baseline/**/.raw-auth/
testdata/visibility-baseline/**/.raw-auth
